items.title: Arturo Gatti Jr., son of late boxing champion, dies at age 17
items.description: Gatti Jr. was 10 months old when his father, who was a world champion in two weight classes, died at age 37 in July 2009.

items.title: Endangered ferrets in more jeopardy as government shutdown drags on
items.description: With biologists from the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service furloughed because of the shutdown, a critical release of 400 captive-bred ferrets is at risk.
